Kogi State Governor, Alhaji Yahaya Bello has ordered the State’s Auditor-General, Alhaji Yakub Okala to conduct a forensic audit of MDAs and institutions caught in the web of Treasury Single Account non-compliance. Governor Bello made this known at the Executive Council meeting held at the expo hall of the Government House in Lokoja. The State Governor had earlier directed the Chief Medical Director of Kogi State Specialist Hospital, Lokoja, Kogi State University Teaching Hospital, Anyingba and Vice-Chancellor and Rector of Kogi State University Anyingba, and Kogi State Polytechnic, Lokoja to proceed on an indefinite suspension after being found wanting of non-remittance into the TSA. ALSO READ: FG files fresh charge against Sowore, Bakare Gov Bello greets Ooni of Ife, Oba Ogunwusi, at 45 INEC confirms Gov Bello’s voters card transfer Nobody can distract Kogi gov from the progress he is making… He mentioned that those that were initially faulted corrected their anomaly within 24 hours when the indefinite suspension was served. Governor Bello reminded the exco members that he swore to an oath to serve the people transparently and he remains responsible to ensure that he and other government officials adhere to such sacred oath. He asserted that the government must ensure transparency as every single dime must be accounted for, noting that his administration would probe itself even before anyone does. The Governor gave a 30 days timeline for the report of the audit to be submitted noting that the outcome would determine if those concerned would keep their jobs. Governor Bello explained that the audit should be within the period when those affected were in charge of affairs at their respective MDAs or institutions. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS